               <head>A compilation of works by Muḥammad ʻAlī Ḥazīn (a-c)</head>
               <msContents class="https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2008112367 https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>A volume containing 3 works by Muḥammad ʻAlī bin ʻAbī Ṭālib bin
							ʻAbd Allāh al-Lāhijī, known as Ḥazīn: a) <title>Dastūr
							al-ʻuqalā</title>, on the ideal qualities and duties of rulers; b)
								<title>Fatḥ al-subul</title>, a Sufi treatise on the nature of God
							and the merits of theology as opposed to philosophy; c)
								<title>Maktūbāt</title>, letters on subjects ranging from the
							numerical properties of letters of the alphabet to the art of poetry. 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 1091a" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1091-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="20v">ff. 1v-20v</locus>
                     <author key="person_50013027">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muḥammad ʻAlī Ḥazīn, ca. 1692- ca.
									1766</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">محمدعلی حزین</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22931">Dastūr al-ʻuqalā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">دستور العقلا</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus n="1v">(f. 1v)</locus> یا واهب التوفیق. و
								یا معطی التحقیق. ثبت لساننا بالصدق. و قلوبنا بالتصدیق 
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus n="20v">(f. 20v)</locus>و سقاه فی المصیر 
								الیه. من کاس المقربین. ممن لدیه لزلفی. و کان 
                     </explicit>
                     <note>
                        <p>The end is defective, indicated by a catchword at the bottom of
									f. 20v followed by a blank page. </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
										the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <ref target="https://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!13_f006r" type="page">Mss Eur E207/13, f. 6r</ref>. 
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 1091b" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1091-item2">
                     <locus from="21v" to="44v">ff. 21v-44v</locus>
                     <author key="person_50013027">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muḥammad ʻAlī Ḥazīn, ca. 1692- ca.
									1766</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">محمد علی حزین</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22213">Fatḥ al-subul</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">فتح السبل</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus n="21v">(f. 21v)</locus> بحمدک یا مفتح
								الابواب. افتح لنا ابواب رحمتک و اقض علینا انوار فضلک 
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus n="44v">(f. 44v)</locus> و در آنچه تبصیص
								کنیم محتاج به برهان و اقامت دلیل نبوده دعوای ما را قایم مقام دلیل
								خواهند داشت. تم
                     </explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus n="44v">(f. 44v)</locus> به اتمام رسید
								رساله فتح السبل من تصنیف شیخ محمدعلی حزین به خط ضعیف المذنب نوازش
								علی 
                     </colophon>
                     <note>
                        <p> A note on f. 44v names the scribe as <persName role="scr" key="person_f8375">Navāzish ʻAlī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
										the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <ref target="https://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!13_f007r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/13, f. 7r</ref>. 
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 1091c" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1091-item3">
                     <author key="person_50013027">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muḥammad ʻAlī Ḥazīn, ca. 1692- ca.
									1766</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">محمد علی حزین</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title key="work_23269" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Maktūbāt</title>
                     <title key="work_23269" xml:lang="fa">مکتوبات</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus n="45v">(f. 45v)</locus> در سلک نظم تهجی حروفی دیدم قرین هم
								مقدم تالی و تالی مقدم.
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus n="50v">(f. 50v)</locus> خیر الوری ... الواثق به عروة ...
								الوثقی محمد المشتهر به علی الزاهدی الجیلانی. ختم الله بالحسنی.
								تم.
                     </explicit>
                     <note>
                        <p>Title is supplied. </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
										the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <ref target="https://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!13_f008r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/13, f. 8r</ref>. 
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
